<map id="Entity Relationship Diagram" name="Entity Relationship Diagram">
<area shape="rect" id="node1" title="dsgrid.config.dataset_config.DatasetConfigModel

Represents dataset configurations.

Attributes:
 &#160;&#160;&#160;dataset_id (str): Unique dataset identifier.
 &#160;&#160;&#160;version (Optional[str]): Version, generated by dsgrid. Default is None.
 &#160;&#160;&#160;dataset_type (InputDatasetType(DSGEnum)): Input dataset type.
 &#160;&#160;&#160;dataset_qualifier_metadata (Optional[QuantityModel, GrowthRateModel]): Additional metadata to include related to the dataset_qualifier. Default is dataset_qualifier_type=&lt;DatasetQualifierType.QUANTITY: &#39;quantity&#39;&gt;.
 &#160;&#160;&#160;sector_description (Optional[str]): Sectoral description (e.g., residential, commercial, industrial, transportation, electricity). Default is None.
 &#160;&#160;&#160;data_source (str): Data source name, e.g. &#39;ComStock&#39;.
 &#160;&#160;&#160;data_schema (Union[StandardDataSchemaModel, OneTableDataSchemaModel]): Schema (table layouts) used for writing out the dataset
 &#160;&#160;&#160;dataset_version (Optional[str]): The version of the dataset. Default is None.
 &#160;&#160;&#160;description (str): A detailed description of the dataset.
 &#160;&#160;&#160;origin_creator (str): Origin data creator&#39;s name (first and last)
 &#160;&#160;&#160;origin_organization (str): Origin organization name, e.g., NREL
 &#160;&#160;&#160;origin_contributors (List[str]): List of origin data contributor&#39;s first and last names e.g., [&quot;Harry Potter&quot;, &quot;Ronald Weasley&quot;]. Default is [].
 &#160;&#160;&#160;origin_project (str): Origin project name
 &#160;&#160;&#160;origin_date (str): Date the source data was generated
 &#160;&#160;&#160;origin_version (str): Version of the origin data
 &#160;&#160;&#160;source (str): Source of the data (text description or link)
 &#160;&#160;&#160;data_classification (DataClassificationType(DSGEnum)): Data security classification (e.g., low, moderate, high)
 &#160;&#160;&#160;tags (List[str]): List of data tags. Default is [].
 &#160;&#160;&#160;enable_unit_conversion (bool): If the dataset uses its dimension mapping for the metric dimension to also perform unit conversion, then this value should be false. Default is True.
 &#160;&#160;&#160;use_project_geography_time_zone (bool): If true, time zones will be applied from the project&#39;s geography dimension. If false, the dataset&#39;s geography dimension records must provide a time zone column. Default is False.
 &#160;&#160;&#160;dimensions (List[Union[DimensionModel, DateTimeDimensionModel, AnnualTimeDimensionModel, RepresentativePeriodTimeDimensionModel, NoOpTimeDimensionModel]]): List of dimensions that make up the dimensions of dataset. They will be automatically registered during dataset registration and then converted to dimension_references. Default is [].
 &#160;&#160;&#160;dimension_references (List[DimensionReferenceModel]): List of registered dimension references that make up the dimensions of dataset. Default is [].
 &#160;&#160;&#160;user_defined_metadata (dict[]): Additional user defined metadata fields. Default is {}.
 &#160;&#160;&#160;trivial_dimensions (Optional[List[DimensionType(DSGEnum)]]): List of trivial dimensions (i.e., 1&#45;element dimensions) that do not exist in the load_data_lookup. List the dimensions by dimension type. Default is [].
 &#160;&#160;&#160;id (Optional[str]): Registry database ID. Default is None.
 &#160;&#160;&#160;key (Optional[str]): Registry database key. Default is None.
 &#160;&#160;&#160;rev (Optional[str]): Registry database revision. Default is None.
" alt="" coords="5,143,1876,927"/>
